<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Cyclox (CYS0130)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Written evidence from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Cyclox</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(CYS0130)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The following was submitted via the committee's website online application form, if I've missed anything, I'm sure it will be covered by one of the numerous other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">knowledgeable submissions</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><br style="clear:both; mso-break-type:section-break; page-break-before:auto" /><div><p style="margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This is the submission by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Cyclox</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of Oxford, for measures that would help safer cycling.   It covers cycle training, enforcement of regulations, infrastructure and planning.</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8688"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8687"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Bikability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> cycle training. Teach across th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e board at school, as widely as swimming is taught. Qualified instructors should be used, not parent/helper volunteers. Children given good quality cycle training are more confident and safer, so will start cycling as a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">life long</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> habit for utility journeys</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Trained cyclists also make for better vehicle drivers in the main. Anecdotal evidence from York - across the board secondary school cycle training was introduced. A few years after, the local driving instructors noticed all their new pupils were a lot mor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e aware of what was going on in the environment around the car as they were driving.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8754"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8753"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Bikability</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> training should be available to others also. Adults returning to cycling after many years not cycling, those who fear traffic, those who need help to ride a bic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ycle in the first place.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8727"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8726"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">well-trained</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> cyclist is the best safety device you can have. £35 spent on cycle training is better than £35 spent on a helmet. Better to avoid the accident in the 1st place, which is what cycle training helps achieve.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8729"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8728"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Better cycl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e awareness training in driver training/driving test for all classes of vehicle, especially buses and HGV's.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8731"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8730"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Better enforcement of traffic laws, with firm penalties applied where necessary. Killing another road user and escaping jail with community service</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> gives rather the wrong message. The risk of jail or a long driving ban will help focus the mind on a better standard of driving.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Introduction of presumed liability (need to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">prove</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> you - driver - are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> at fault in case of an accident with a vulnerable roa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d user). NB, applies for appo</span><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8735"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rtioning fault/responsibility for an accident, and for damages - </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">not for criminal prosecution cases</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Often the victim can't make a case as they don't even remember the accident happening.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8739"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8738"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Default 20 mph limits in towns - shown </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to reduce accidents, and will make for a more conducive environment to walk/cycle/play/live/work in.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 42.35pt; orphans:0; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8737"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8736"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Lower speed limits on rural roads (which have quite a bad accident record).</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 46.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8752"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8751"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Ensure all highway engineers and designers are competent in the design/construc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tion of cycle facilities - currently this is often not the case. Training </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">needs to be done to ensure effective use of public money</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 46.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Design road space to encourage and enable cycling/make it feel and be safe. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 46.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8749"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8748"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8750"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Allocate dedicated budget resources to allow abo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ve - hard to ask for in current economic climate, but the investment will bring an excellent return. Often designing cycle friendly infrastructure is as much about how you design – a good design can be a similar cost to a bad design. You build/repair the s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ame stuff, but have it in slightly different places.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 46.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Where (mostly main) roads and junctions have their once in 20 – 30 year rebuild (as happens in Oxfordshire), currently highway engineers try their best to replace like with like. Persuading the highway a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">uthority to make significant changes is very difficult. Periodic maintenance works such as these rarely even get consulted on. If highway authorities were required to consult on and make roads/junctions cycle (and pedestrian) friendly in each 20 – 30 year </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">make over, the extra cost of making it cycle friendly is low, as the whole thing is being rebuilt anyway. The only thing is some parts are rebuilt slightly differently. If this was adopted, in 20 – 30 years, a major part of the county's busy road  network </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">would be make cycle/pedestrian friendly for minimal extra cost.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 0pt 46.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8743"></a><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8745"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Where one off government grants are made available to local authorities for cycling related infrastructure projects, the time scale for design/construction/completion needs to be long enough t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o allow enough time for the best design to be implemented. Often time scales are not long enough, so a rushed/inappropriate/less effective scheme is implemented simply to get the government money. Government assessment of schemes submitted needs to be much</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> better than currently to ensure good designs and good value for money.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 0pt 46.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8744"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Enable cycling to link into the public transport network. Adequate/secure cyc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">le parking at rail stations/bus-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">stations/bus stops. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 28.35pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 28.35pt 14.15pt 46.35pt; orphans:0; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><a name="yui_3_7_2_1_1389901702206_8828"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">All new developments should be cycle/walking friendl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">y - so the car is no longer deemed required for local journeys. No long circuitous routes for short walking/cycling journeys, all free from busy/threatening road conditions.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Planning requirements for cycle parking provision at residential/business developm</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ents are enforced. For people to feel able to use their bikes, they need to be confident there will be a secure parking place at their destination to help prevent theft of their cycle. One quarter of those who have a cycle stolen give up cycling and don't </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">replace their cycle.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>